c WMC regression for DVE weight folding.
c x1<->x2 (x2 definable by x1); x2 has an ASYMMETRIC weight whose two sides
c collide at 15 significant figures but differ in exact value
c (1/3 vs 100000000000000000003/300000000000000000000).
c Two bugs this guards against:
c  - candidate selection must use exact equals(), not to_string() (else x2 is
c    wrongly taken as weight-symmetric and eliminated);
c  - when DVE does eliminate a (symmetric) definable var, its weight must be
c    folded into weight_factor (else the count is off by that weight).
c Exact answer (all vars projected): w1*w2 + w1n*w2n with the weights below
c   = 250000000000000000003/1200000000000000000000.
c t wmc
p cnf 5 5
c p weight 1 1/2 0
c p weight -1 1/2 0
c p weight 2 1/3 0
c p weight -2 100000000000000000003/300000000000000000000 0
c p weight 3 1/2 0
c p weight -3 1/2 0
c p weight 4 1/2 0
c p weight -4 1/2 0
c p weight 5 1/2 0
c p weight -5 1/2 0
1 -2 0
-1 2 0
1 3 4 0
2 4 5 0
3 -5 0
